{#
  booking.jinja2 — Calendar booking message (qualified lead)
  Tenacious Consulting & Outsourcing SDR Agent

  Required variables:
    contact_first_name  (str) — prospect's first name
    company_name        (str) — prospect company name
    brief_summary       (str) — 2-sentence recap of what the agent learned during
                                qualification (initiative + constraint). Written by
                                the agent from answered Q1–Q4, not fabricated.
    calendar_link       (str) — Cal.com booking URL (must be confirmed non-null
                                before this template is rendered)
    sender_name         (str) — name shown in signature

  Purpose: This message is sent only after is_qualified == True. The prospect has
  already indicated interest and answered all qualification questions. Do not re-pitch.
  Do not introduce new information. Just close the loop and hand off to a human call.

  Guardrail notes:
    - tone_checker.enforce() must be called on the rendered output before send.
    - No asks beyond the calendar link — they have already said yes in principle.
    - bench_guard must confirm availability for the relevant specialty before this
      message is sent; if the bench is at zero, escalate to a human SDR instead.
#}

{{ contact_first_name }},

Here is what I have on my end:

{{ brief_summary }}

That is a solid basis for a 25-minute call. One of our technical leads will walk through
squad composition, stack alignment, and what week one would actually look like.

Grab time here: {{ calendar_link }}

The link goes straight to their calendar — no back-and-forth needed.

{{ sender_name }}
Tenacious Consulting & Outsourcing
